8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Canva and Crello share a solid foundation of core features including Templates, Drag And Drop, Brand Kit, Collaboration. Where Canva pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Ai Generation and Responsive and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Canva holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10, while Crello scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Canva and Crello offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Canva's free tier and Crello's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
